Body: Description: SEEK System Scan not returning results against a Windows Filer. Verified the collection is functional against the localhost.
Brandon was able to get me access, permissions are good. I was able to add the customer as a collaborator and sent them the link. Just waiting on them now.
What We've Learned Updated: No errors found by dev in the logs provided so far

Next Steps Updated: Get the following from the customer:
- Latest FSAA and SEEK job folders with their entire log structures
--- If either is too large, a screenshot the structures so the dev team can advise which items can be omitted from the collection

Invitation updated. Attendees: Tay Caliguiri, Jeff Forsyth

2. Run SEEK scan and import jobs
3. Observe no data

What We've Learned Updated: No errors found by dev in the logs provided so far. SEEK System scan acts the same in local and automatic scanning modes.
Next Steps Updated: Waiting on R&D

@Jeff Forsyth​ This appears to be related to a known issue we have with a few other customers. To expedite the investigation of this, please update the ticket with the correct contact from the customer so we can continue. I will need to collect the debug job logs, and the Windows Event Application log from the customer in order to confirm our suspicions. 

 

Has this job been run since November '24? Despite the logs being uploaded recently, there are no updated runs from 2025. There is also a running.lck file in the SEEK System Scan folder.

Next Steps Updated: A fix was published in December 2024 for the Senstive Data add-on where resource consumption would grow unexpected and the scan would produce and out of memory or similar errors then crash. NEA 11.6.0.125 and SDD 11.6.0.14. We would need to know the most recent build of NEA nad the SDD Add-on to determine that this fix is implemented.

What We've Learned Updated: At this time we have not received recent or artifacts demonstrating a true failure of Netwrix Enterprise Auditor.  We have seen evidence of the scan abruptly ending. We asked and did not receive any indication from you if there were sudden resource spikes around this time.

We have been unable to to identify any indication of malfuction except for this abrupt ending which may be cause by any number of external factors.
